name: Warung Babi Guling Yan Asih
address: HC78+RGX, Jl. Raya Besakih, Nongan, Kec. Rendang, Kabupaten Karangasem, Bali 80863, Indonesia
review 1:
Outstanding!
The pork was just perfect, the skin crunchy like caramel and the meat so tender!
The sides were also excellent. Particularly the coconut pork sate.
Accomodating, helpful and fast service.
Fresh and big venue.
review 2:
My guide asked me to stop here to try it
Its apparently not as good as the Babi Guling Ibu Oka in Ubud but its good
They have ears and other parts too and vege (careful, it is üå∂Ô∏è)
Didnt like that they picked the pork up via their hands. But otherwise, taste was good. üëç
review 3: The most delicious babi guling on the island. While the other famous babi guling in Ubud/Denpasar/Nusa Dua area  normally quiet spicy and salty, this one just taste perfect. The spice just mixed well. Not too spicy (unless we take the sambal) but we can taste the "base genep"in all "component".  we bought the jumbo portion, the skin was super crunchy - maybe bcos we were there in the morning. The price worth the food and service.
review 4: Ive been to Bali many times and taste different Babi Guling. We were on our way to Besakih and we decided to try it here. You wont be disappointed. It taste better than the ‚Äúpopular‚Äù Babi Guling Warung. The spice is on point, the Lawar, the Pork, the hospitality. 10 stars!
review 5: Delicious, cheap and affordable, the owner is enthusiastic, highly recommended
